Class IterableGeneratorBridge<S,​T>

Object
IterableGeneratorBridge<S,​T>
Type Parameters:
S - source-type
T - destination-type
All Implemented Interfaces:
Generator, IterableGenerator<S>, WritableItem
public class IterableGeneratorBridge<S,​T>
extends Object
implements Generator, IterableGenerator<S>
Allows us to call an IterableGenerator<S> as if it was an IterableGenerator<T>

Owen Feehan

    • createOneToOne

      public static <S,​ T> IterableGeneratorBridge<S,​T> createOneToOne​(IterableGenerator<T> generator, CheckedFunction<S,​T,​?> bridge)
      Creates a bridge that maps ONE-TO-ONE from source to destination (i.e. one call to the generator for each source item)
      Type Parameters:
      S - source-type
      T - destination-type
      Parameters:
      generator - the generator that accepts the destination type
      bridge - maps a source-item to one destination-item
      Returns:
      a generator that accepts source-types as iterators, but actually calls a generator that uses destination types
